Consider the following code snippet. What will be the most likely output?

```java
Thread t = new Thread(() -> System.out.print("Hello"));
t.start();
System.out.print(t.isAlive() ? "Alive" : "Not Alive");
```

Analyze the following code. What is a key issue with its attempt to use the result from a thread?

```java
class Calculator implements Runnable {
    public int result;
    public void run() {
        result = calculate();
    }
    private int calculate() { /* Long calculation */ return 42; }
}

public class Test {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Calculator c = new Calculator();
        Thread t = new Thread(c);
        t.start();
        System.out.println("The result is: " + c.result);
    }
}
```
